==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shipworm
<hw>Ship"worm`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any long, slender, worm-shaped bivalve mollusk of <gen>Teredo</gen>
and allied genera. The shipworms burrow in wood, and are destructive to
wooden ships, piles of wharves, etc. See <er>Teredo</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shipwreck</ent>⟦br⟧
